%N A394967 Decimal expansion of sqrt(3)/(2*Pi) - log(2)/(4*sqrt(3)) - 1/6.
%H A394967 H. F. Sandham, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1093/qmath/3.1.179">Two identities due to Ramanujan</a>, The Quarterly Journal of Mathematics, Vol. 3, No. 1 (1952), pp. 179-182.
%F A394967 Equals A002194/A019692 - A379101/A002194 - 1/6.
%F A394967 Equals Sum_{k>=1} p(k)/(2*cosh(sqrt(24*k-1)*Pi/3) - 1), where p(k) = A000041(k) is the number of partitions of k (Sandham, 1952). Note that in the paper log(2) should be log(2)/4.
%e A394967 0.00895060322315071832690462815325700005092168933147379...
%t A394967 RealDigits[Sqrt[3]/(2*Pi) - Log[2]/(4*Sqrt[3]) - 1/6, 10, 120, -1][[1]]
%o A394967 (PARI) sqrt(3)/(2*Pi) - log(2)/(4*sqrt(3)) - 1/6
